To make marinade, mix all ingredients in a heavy plastic bag or small bowl. Add meat and marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes or in refrigerator up to 4 hours or overnight. Place oven rack 4-inches from broiler. Line a broiler pan with heavy foil. Spray with cooking spray. To assemble kabobs, alternate 2 pieces of beef, peppers, mushrooms and apples on skewers. Brush with marinade. Broil for 3 minutes. Turn, brush with marinade and broil 3 minutes for medium.